Real-Time Fraud Detection System

PROJECT OBJECTIVE

The objective of this project was to develop a machine learning-based fraud detection system capable of identifying fraudulent financial transactions efficiently. The project focuses on detecting anomalies in transaction behavior using advanced classification models, explainable AI, and interactive visualizations.

------------------------------------------------------------

DATASET USED

The project uses the IEEE-CIS Fraud Detection dataset from Kaggle.

Datasets Used:
• train_transaction.csv
• train_identity.csv

Both datasets were merged using the TransactionID column.

------------------------------------------------------------

DATA PREPROCESSING

Several preprocessing techniques were applied:

• Missing value handling
• Feature engineering
• Label encoding
• Data scaling
• Class imbalance handling using SMOTE

New features such as HourOfDay and AmtToMeanRatio were created to improve fraud prediction performance.

------------------------------------------------------------

MODELS IMPLEMENTED

The following machine learning models were implemented:

• LightGBM
• XGBoost
• Isolation Forest

Among these, LightGBM achieved the best overall performance due to its strong Recall, F1-Score, and PR-AUC values.

------------------------------------------------------------

EXPLAINABLE AI USING SHAP

SHAP (SHapley Additive Explanations) was used to interpret model predictions and identify the most important fraud indicators.

Top fraud indicators identified:
• Transaction Amount
• Transaction Timing
• Amount Ratio Features

------------------------------------------------------------

DASHBOARD DEVELOPMENT

An interactive Streamlit dashboard was developed to visualize:

• Fraud probability
• Risk segmentation
• Transaction analysis
• Fraud trends

The dashboard allows users to explore transactions and filter by risk tiers.

------------------------------------------------------------

KEY FINDINGS

• Fraudulent transactions generally had higher transaction amounts.
• Suspicious transactions often occurred during unusual hours.
• LightGBM provided the best fraud detection performance.
• Explainable AI improved model transparency and interpretability.

------------------------------------------------------------

CONCLUSION

The project successfully developed a complete fraud detection pipeline using machine learning, explainable AI, and dashboard deployment. The system can help financial organizations reduce fraud losses, improve transaction monitoring, and strengthen fraud prevention strategies.